<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="L-functions" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>L-Functions</title>
  <p>
    Let <m>f \in M_k(\Gamma_1(N))</m> and 
    <me>
        f = \sum_{n = 0}^{\infty} a_n(f)q^n
    </me>
    The associated L-function is
    <me>
        L(f,s) = \sum_{n = 1}^{\infty} \frac{a_n(f)}{n^s}
    </me>
    the series converges for <m>\text{Re}(s) >> 0</m> since <m>a_n(f) = O(n^{k + \epsilon})</m>. Also this gives us a complex analytic function in some half plane.
    <me>
        \Lambda(s) = (\frac{2 \pi}{N})^{-s} \Gamma(s)L(f,s)
    </me>
    This has interesting properties
    <ol>
        <li>
            <p>
                This has an analytic continuation to all of <m>\mathbb{C}</m> if <m>f \in \S_k(\Gamma_1(N))</m> and a meromorphic continuation to <m>\mathbb{C}</m> in general with respect to the only possible poles being at <m>s = k,0</m> for <m>-k \in \mathbb{N}</m>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                The desired functional equation is
                <me>
                    \Lambda(f,s) = i^k\Lambda(g,k-s)
                </me>
                where <m>g = f \mid_k w_N \: (g \in M_k(\Gamma_1(N)))</m> and <m>w_N = \begin{pmatrix}
                    0 \amp -1 \\
                    N \amp 0
                \end{pmatrix}
                </m>

            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
    Suppose <m>f</m> is a simultaneous eigenform for all <m>T_n</m>'s. Then we have,
    <ol>
        <li>
            <p>
                <m>a_1(f) \neq 0</m> (so, let's assume <m>a_1(f) = 1</m>)
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                <m>L(f,s) = \prod_{l \nmid N} (1 - a_l(f)l^{-s} + \chi(l)l^{k - 1 - 2s})^{-1} \prod_{l \mid N} (1 - a_l(f)l^{-s})^{-1}</m>
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
  </p>
      <theorem>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Let <m>f \in S_k(N,\chi)</m> be a new-form of weight <m>k</m> and level <m>N</m> then
                <me>
                    g = f \mid_k w_N = c_f . f_p
                </me>
                where <m>c_f \in \mathbb{C}</m> is constant and <m>f_p = \sum_{n = 1}^{\infty} \overline{a_n(f)}q^n</m>. Moreover <m>f_p</m> is a new-form.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </theorem>

</section>